00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:14,852
to see how reliable you are.

253
00:10:14,852 --> 00:10:16,440
I know it seems crazy

254
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,915
that you have to use debt
to be seen as reliable

255
00:10:18,915 --> 00:10:20,760
but that's just the way it is.

256
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:23,460
So instead of thinking
that debt is always bad

257
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:26,700
try to understand how to
use it to your advantage.

258
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:29,370
Step six, don't spend earned money.

259
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:30,300
When it comes to money,

260
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:33,270
there's a common misconception
that the more money you make,

261
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:34,980
the more money you should spend.

262
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:37,830
However, this couldn't be
further from the truth.

263
00:10:37,830 --> 00:10:41,040
In fact, the key to having
a consistently great life

264
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:44,460
is to spend only what your
investment portfolio yields.

265
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:46,770
This is normally around eight to 10%.

266
00:10:46,770 --> 00:10:48,750
I'm not saying to actually
take the money out

267
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:51,191
of your investments just
to spend that percentage

268
00:10:51,191 --> 00:10:54,330
of your earnings, I know
this can sound confusing,

269
00:10:54,330 --> 00:10:57,519
so for example, if you
have $1 million invested

270
00:10:57,519 --> 00:11:00,930
then you'd be able to spend
up to 10% of that value

271
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:03,150
which is $100,000 per year

272
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:05,940
from your earnings without
having to worry too much.

273
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:08,370
Of course, this does
rely on you making a lot

274
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:10,590
but once you've made it to step six,

275
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:12,240
this shouldn't be too much of an issue.

276
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,520
Think of it this way,
every dollar you earn

277
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,470
is like a seed that you can plant

278
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:18,840
and watch grow into a money tree.

279
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:22,260
The more seed you plant, the
bigger your portfolio becomes

280
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:24,000
and the more money it will yield.

281
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,250
And just like a tree, if you take care

282
